Installation procedure
----------------------

scramv1 p CMSSW CMSSW_1_6_9
cd CMSSW_1_6_9/src
project CMSSW
eval `scramv1 runtime -sh`
[ eval `scramv1 runtime -csh` if you use a c-shell]

addpkg RecoEcal/EgammaClusterAlgos
addpkg RecoEcal/EgammaClusterProducers

# getting all the S9 clustering files, to be copied in the appropriate places
cvs co UserCode/ferriff/S9Clustering

cp UserCode/ferriff/S9Clustering/S9ClusterAlgo*.h RecoEcal/EgammaClusterAlgos/interface
cp UserCode/ferriff/S9Clustering/S9Cluster*Algo.cc RecoEcal/EgammaClusterAlgos/src
cp UserCode/ferriff/S9Clustering/BuildFile_Algos RecoEcal/EgammaClusterAlgos/BuildFile

cp UserCode/ferriff/S9Clustering/S9*Producer.h RecoEcal/EgammaClusterProducers/interface/
cp UserCode/ferriff/S9Clustering/S9*Producer.cc RecoEcal/EgammaClusterProducers/src/
cp UserCode/ferriff/S9Clustering/SealModule.cc RecoEcal/EgammaClusterProducers/src/SealModule.cc
cp UserCode/ferriff/S9Clustering/BuildFile_Producers RecoEcal/EgammaClusterProducers/BuildFile
cp UserCode/ferriff/S9Clustering/S9SuperClusters.cfi RecoEcal/EgammaClusterProducers/data
cp UserCode/ferriff/S9Clustering/TestS9Producer.cfg RecoEcal/EgammaClusterProducers/test

scramv1 b

cd RecoEcal/EgammaClusterProducers/test

# edit TestS9Producer.cfg to read the file and the number of events you whish
cmsRun TestS9Producer.cfg
